AB  - Emerging Engineering Education (EEE) is crucial for training engineering and technical personnel, and colleges are actively building student practice bases. However, new engineering education requires interconnection across multiple disciplines and has issues such as the contradiction between strict laboratory equipment management and the independent learning needs of students. Utilizing the rich data from our university's Emerging Engineering Research & Development Building, we have constructed an intelligent agent using large models and a digital twin system of the building to provide personalized guidance for student academic planning and equipment management. We have also developed a multi-agent framework to generate learning path plans and course equipment suggestions, supporting multi-round dialogue iterative learning. We developed the digital twin system with unity and the digital human system with Motionverse. The demonstration presents a solution for new engineering education and its application potential.
