AB  - The article examines the impact of Open Engineering Education on the digital transformation of the social sphere. We focus on the methods of Open Engineering Education as a tool to eliminate interregional inequality and provide universal access to educational resources through its digitalization. The paper analyzes how the trends in the digitalization of education affect the development of its infrastructure within Education 4.0. We propose the concept of Open Engineering Education, which implements individual learning paths, and formulate recommendations on adapting teaching practice to changing requirements in the context of Education 4.0.
