AB  - Learning Factory is a modern innovative approach that enables the environment for training, education, or research purpose. The model is conducted and widely applied not only in the domain of academia but the field of production, manufacturing, and industry. Practices have shown undeniable benefits, however, difficulties and challenges in conventional learning factory construction still remain as the model demands certain tremendous effort, concerning room/space, the ability to new content adaptation, or the cost of equipment investment. This paper aims to present cases and approaches in digitalizing the Learning Factory concept, by adopting one of the essential keys related to Industry 4.0 – the Digital Twins technology through the development of the Complete Digital Learning Factory (CDLF). The developed digital Learning Factory shows its potential to tackle the aforementioned obstacles as it requires nearly no room/space and equipment for the learning environment, while concurrently depicting the structure of physical systems, thus promoting the operation of a planned Learning Factory model without being deterred by physical limitations.
