AB  - Scheduling optimization is still more and more important issue in mass customization manufacturing. Its goal is to overcome one of the drawbacks of mass customization for consumers, which is longer delivery times comparing with manufacturing of standard products. The main goal of this paper is to propose the possible solution to minimize processing cycle times, which is basic condition to shorten overall delivery times. Moreover, the suggested method encompasses identification of optimally modular assembly process structure from alternative ones. Exploration of this scheduling optimization problem was conducted using simulation software Tecnomatix Plant Simulation and brought relevant findings for the field.
