AB  - Optimizing of husker processes parameters is essential for achieving of higher productivity and high quality products in order to remain competitive. This research investigates multi-objective optimization of paddy husking machine for an optimal parametric combination to provide the maximum percentage of the wholeness of brown rice using the Grey relational analysis. Husker process parameters considered are spindle speed, clearance and temperature. Twenty seven experimental runs based on Taguchi’s L-27 (33) orthogonal array were performed followed by the Grey relational analysis to solve the multi-response optimization problem. Based on the Grey relational grade value, optimum levels of parameters have been identified. The results prove the potential of design of experiments, ANOVA analysis with Grey relational analysis and Taguchi method in multi-objective optimization of husker process parameters.
