AB  - The future benefits of a stroller which transforms into a double one are not considered when selling and promoting products. The lack of incentives for companies, the interests these practices generate, and the need to create a culture of more responsible use of objects, contribute to the scant interest in designing products which minimize the “use and discard” behavior. However, it would be interesting to determine the extent of awareness of a more rational use of objects and how it can be increased. To this end, a joint study with the company BabyEssentials was conducted to assess whether the positive perception of a promotional video - showcasing a product with longer lifespan due to its ability to adapt to future user needs compared to a commercial one - is perceived by users with and without prior experience of the product.
