AB  - This paper presents a detailed technical exploration of integrating low-cost multi-function instruments within the MICRO remote laboratory to optimize microcontroller-based experiments. We specifically detail the implementation and configuration of the Analog and Digital Discovery series, which can be used to facilitate real-time data acquisition and remote control. Our approach focuses on the technical challenges and solutions in embedding these tools into an existing remote lab setup, enabling enhanced interaction capabilities and practical application of theoretical concepts. The integration process demonstrates a significant improvement in handling complex experiments remotely and provides a scalable, cost-effective method to enrich remote engineering education. By addressing the specific technical adaptations required for these instruments, this paper aims to advance the capabilities and reach of remote laboratories.
