AB  - In the next few years, the IoT sector is expected to exhibit a robust growth of around 17% annually. This growth is powered and sustained by the increased investments in AI and cybersecurity. Moreover, in recent years the sensor market has significantly grown due to technological advancements and industry demands. A key factor contributing to this growth is related to integrating sensors in consumer electronics, industrial applications, or automotive. The future of innovation, technology, and industrial advancement is significantly influenced by engineering education. Engineering schools, like “Transylvania” University with the Center for Valorization and Transfer of Competences CVTC, continue actively to mold the next generation of engineers, greatly enhancing society and technology as CVTC is recognized as a sustaining collaboration between academia and industry. This paper promotes and sustains all these ideas, building and testing new IoT flexible monitoring systems specially designed for students’ training and involvement in future research activities.
