AB  - Cyber-physical laboratories have become a reality in the education scene in the past decade, especially with the difficult events the world has witnessed in the last three years. Cyber-physical laboratories are particularly important in distance and blended learning environments as they offer several benefits and advantages. However, as in other cyber-physical systems, the labs generate large amounts of data that make them vulnerable to cyber-attacks and single-point of failure. Blockchain is a suitable technology for cyber-physical laboratories as it empowers them to preserve data integrity and to minimize cyber-attacks. A blockchain-based cyber-physical lab employing an Ethereum platform, an Interplanetary File System (IPFS), and IoT devices programmed in LabVIEW, is presented in order to provide a proof-of-concept and to demonstrate the viability of the proposed solution. The lab experiments are hence conducted in a decentralized and secure manner that ensures students’ privacy and the learning process integrity.
