AB  - Remote laboratories are hardware and software tools that allow students to access the actual equipment via the Internet. Remote laboratory management systems (RLMS) are software tools developed to create remote laboratories more simply, providing some of the common features cross most remote laboratories (such as authentication, authorization, planning platforms and administrative tools) and certain protocols or APIs (Application Programming Interfaces) for the creation of laboratories. Work on laboratory experiments and project work requires access to expensive hardware equipment. The high cost of these instruments and the long development process of experimentation in the educational process create a significant bottleneck. There is a need for the development of a laboratory remotely using which users can remotely access laboratory instruments and programmable devices on their smartphones/tablets to perform laboratory experiments. The development of remote laboratories is a promising direction for the future of engineering education because they provide means for students to design and conduct experiments without the need for physical laboratories equipment on site.Our work consists in realizing a remote laboratory, based in artificial intelligence, which includes experiences in physics. For sharing these experiences with several organizations on a national and international scale.
