AB  - Introduction. The article presents a comprehensive study and justification of scientific and practical approaches to the integration of computer-aided design (CAD) systems into modern production processes using innovative technologies. The purpose of this scientific work is a comprehensive analysis of the current state, challenges and prospects for the implementation of computer-aided design (CAD) systems into scientific and production activities in Ukraine. The article aims to identify key barriers that hinder the full integration of CAD into the national innovation space, in particular into the scientific programs of technical universities, research practices and production processes of the real sector of the economy. The degree of readiness of domestic institutions to use modern software solutions of the CAD/CAM/CAE class is also investigated, taking into account personnel, infrastructure, regulatory and financial constraints. Results.  The focus of the study is the development of approaches to the formation of a system of scientific and technical policy focused on the development of a digital engineering environment in Ukraine. In particular, it concerns the need to form state and inter-sectoral priorities in the field of computer-aided design, promote the modernization of specialized programs by implementing international standards for training specialists in the field of CAD/CAM technologies, as well as create effective interaction between universities, research institutes and industrial enterprises. Conclusion. An important goal of the article is to outline the current world experience in implementing CAD and assess its relevance for Ukrainian realities, in particular in terms of the use of open and cloud technologies, the widespread use of STEM/STEAM principles, as well as the role of such tools as digital twins, PLM systems (product lifecycle management) and virtual laboratories. Thus, the article is aimed not only at identifying problems, but also at forming a basis for developing practical recommendations for increasing competitiveness, technical education and industry in the context of global digitalization.
